Kanban Board - Task Manager

A modern, responsive Kanban board application for managing tasks efficiently. Organize your work into three columns: **To Do**, **In Progress**, and **Completed**. Built with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and Font Awesome icons.

Features

âœ¨Task Management

- Create new tasks with title and description
- Organize tasks across three status columns (To Do, In Progress, Completed)
- Set priority levels for each task (Low, Medium, High)
- Add due dates to tasks
- Edit existing tasks
- Delete tasks

ðŸŽ¨ User Experience

- Clean and modern UI with Tailwind CSS
- Responsive design that works on desktop and mobile
- Icon-rich interface using Font Awesome
- Task counters for each column
- Gradient navbar with intuitive navigation

ðŸ’¾ Data Persistence

- Automatic saving to browser's local storage
- Tasks persist between sessions
- No server required

Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: HTML5, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- **Icons**: Font Awesome 6.5.1
- **Storage**: Browser LocalStorage
- **Build**: TypeScript Compiler

Getting Started

1. Open `index.html` in your web browser
2. Click the **+** button in the navbar to add a new task
3. Fill in the task details (title, description, priority, due date)
4. Click **Submit** to create the task
5. Drag tasks between columns or use the status dropdown to change their status
6. Click **Edit** to modify existing tasks
7. Click **Delete** to remove tasks

